{
  "texts": [
    "To achieve more consistent performance, practitioners frequently fine-tune models using parameter-efficient fine-tuning methods (PEFT) [180], [181].",
    "Although effective in stabilizing outputs, this fine-tuning typically compromises the model's generalization capabilities, resulting in overfitting to a narrow instruction set.",
    "Additionally, PEFT introduces computational overhead and increases deployment time, making the deployment pipeline more resource-intensive.In this survey, we formally define these phenomena as key challenges for speech LLMs in speech understanding tasks.",
    "As a preliminary step, we conduct empirical evaluations to quantify their effects.",
    "To assess acoustic perception sensitivity, we employ automatic speech recognition (ASR) and gender recognition (GR) tasks."
  ]
}